basics.name: Jing Ting Zheng
basics.label: Student
basics.summary: I am studying for a B.S. in Computer Science in the Department of Information and Computer Sciences at the University of Hawaii. I expect to graduate in December 2024.

highlights: Develop web applications for affective computing using JavaScript, Flask (Python), HTML, CSS
Organize monthly volunteer projects and events to increase civic engagement in students
Oversee product development and communication for a civic engagement web application to facilitate community service events and opportunities
Performed data wrangling and statistical analyses using SAS on complex and large datasets
Implemented data visualization techniques to showcase findings on the topic of comparing dietary indices in children and adults in the Pacific
Analyzed Youth Risk Behavior Surveillance System data using statistical analyses in R and communicated results using data visualizations

volunteer.position: Computer Science Research Mentorship Program Scholar
highlights: Receive valuable mentorship from Google engineers and scientists to support my pursuit of computing research and develop computing area expertise, technical, and research skills
Prepare materials for college and career center workshops
Provided tips and mentorship for students applying to colleges and feedback on applications
Investigated the societal and ethical impacts of artificial intelligence and data processing
Learned about the applications and technical concepts of the different types of machine learning
Vice President, Supporting Women in Information Technology & Computing (SWITCH), 2022-Present
Vice Chair, Association for Computing Machinery Women Chapter, 2022-Present
Member, Association for Computing Machinery Manoa Chapter, 2021-Present

awards.title: Undergraduate Research Project Funding Recipient
